cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image quality assessment and evaluation of blind IQA algorithms. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper discusses the creation of a new image quality database and the use of a crowdsourcing system for a large-scale subjective study. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the study involves human observers and their subjective opinions on image quality. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the evaluation of automatic perceptual quality prediction models. 
- cs.MM (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper evaluates blind IQA algorithms, which may involve machine learning techniques.
